BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script in background (enter directly as text)
BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: tell application "System Events"	set frontApp to name of first application process whose frontmost is true	display dialog "Quit?"end telltell application frontApp to quit

BTTTriggers.BTTTriggerTypeDescription: TipSwipe Left Finger Up (2 Fingers Fix)

BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes" to playpauseelse	tell application "Spotify" to playpauseend if

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is playing then			return (get artist of current track) & " - " & (get name of current track)		else			return "▶︎"		end if	end tellend ifif application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is playing then			return (get artist of current track) & " - " & (get name of current track)		else			return "▶︎"		end if	end tellend ifreturn "▶︎"

BTTTriggers.BTTTriggerTypeDescription: TipSwipe Left Finger Down (2 Fingers Fix)

BTTAdditionalActions.BTTPredefinedActionName: Close currently open Touch Bar group
Run Apple Script in background (enter directly as text)
Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTAdditionalActions.BTTInlineAppleScript: activate application "Activity Monitor"tell application "System Events"	tell process "Activity Monitor"		tell radio button "CPU" of radio group 1 of group 2 of toolbar 1 of window 1 to perform action "AXPress"	end tellend tell

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: set cpu to do shell script "ps axo %cpu | awk '{s+=$1}END{print s}'"return cpu & "%"

BTTAdditionalActions.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTAdditionalActions.BTTInlineAppleScript: activate application "Activity Monitor"tell application "System Events"	tell process "Activity Monitor"		tell radio button "Memory" of radio group 1 of group 2 of toolbar 1 of window 1 to perform action "AXPress"	end tellend tell

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: set mem to do shell script "ps -A -o %mem | awk '{s+=$1}END{print s}'"return mem & "%"

BTTAdditionalActions.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTAdditionalActions.BTTInlineAppleScript: activate application "Activity Monitor"tell application "System Events"	tell process "Activity Monitor"		tell radio button "Energy" of radio group 1 of group 2 of toolbar 1 of window 1 to perform action "AXPress"	end tellend tell

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: do shell script "pmset -g batt | grep InternalBattery | column -t"set x to the resultset percentage to word 6 of xset state to word 7 of xset t1 to word 8 of xset t2 to word 9 of xset remaining to the word 10 of xif remaining contains "remaining" then	if state is "discharging" then		return "⬇" & percentage & "% | " & t1 & ":" & t2 & " remaining"	else if state is "charging" then		return "⬆" & percentage & "% | " & t1 & ":" & t2	else		return percentage	end ifelse	return percentageend if

if application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is not paused then			return " "		else			return ""		end if	end tellend ifif application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is not paused then			return " "		else			return ""		end if	end tellend ifreturn ""
